-- European Union Carbon Allowances Climb 1.1% in London's Climate Exchange
-- Ewa Krukowska
-- 2010-06-28T06:04:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/european-union-carbon-allowances-climb-1-1-in-london-s-climate-exchange.html

          
          
             Carbon permits under the European
Union’s emissions-trading system, the world’s biggest
cap-and-trade program, rose 1.1 percent.  
 EU allowances for December 2010 delivery traded at 15.42
euros a metric ton as of 7:04 a.m. on London’s European Climate
Exchange, compared with 15.25 euros at the close of the previous
session.   
